                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4A6/393: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-13T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 13, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Your 44, July 13 [<hi rend="italic">12</hi>], 3 p.m. Delegates should remain
                    Geneva pending further instructions. Telegraph full final text to Department <pb
                        facs="0785" n="671" xml:id="pg_671"/> and to Berne for forwarding to Wilson,
                    asking Wilson urgently to telegraph comments to you and to Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
